{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9cd3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"11302"},"text":"§ 11302.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" General definition of homeless individual","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9cd4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this chapter, the terms “homeless”, “homeless individual”, and “homeless person” means— ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn003993"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn003993"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. Probably should be “mean—”."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9cd5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" an individual or family who lacks a fixed, regular, and adequate nighttime residence;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9cd6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" an individual or family with a primary nighttime residence that is a public or private place not designed for or ordinarily used as a regular sleeping accommodation for human beings, including a car, park, abandoned building, bus or train station, airport, or camping ground;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9cd7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" an individual or family living in a supervised publicly or privately operated shelter designated to provide temporary living arrangements (including hotels and motels paid for by Federal, State, or local government programs for low-income individuals or by charitable organizations, congregate shelters, and transitional housing);","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9cd8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" an individual who resided in a shelter or place not meant for human habitation and who is exiting an institution where he or she temporarily resided;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9cd9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" an individual or family who—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9cda-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a/5/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" will imminently lose their housing, including housing they own, rent, or live in without paying rent, are sharing with others, and rooms in hotels or motels not paid for by Federal, State, or local government programs for low-income individuals or by charitable organizations, as evidenced by—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9cdb-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a/5/A/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a court order resulting from an eviction action that notifies the individual or family that they must leave within 14 days;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9cdc-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a/5/A/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the individual or family having a primary nighttime residence that is a room in a hotel or motel and where they lack the resources necessary to reside there for more than 14 days; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9cdd-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a/5/A/iii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iii"},"text":"(iii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" credible evidence indicating that the owner or renter of the housing will not allow the individual or family to stay for more than 14 days, and any oral statement from an individual or family seeking homeless assistance that is found to be credible shall be considered credible evidence for purposes of this clause;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9cde-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a/5/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" has no subsequent residence identified; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9cdf-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a/5/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" lacks the resources or support networks needed to obtain other permanent housing; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9ce0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" unaccompanied youth and homeless families with children and youth defined as homeless under other Federal statutes who—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9ce1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a/6/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" have experienced a long term period without living independently in permanent housing,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9ce2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a/6/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" have experienced persistent instability as measured by frequent moves over such period, and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9ce3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/a/6/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" can be expected to continue in such status for an extended period of time because of chronic disabilities, chronic physical health or mental health conditions, substance addiction, histories of domestic violence or childhood abuse, the presence of a child or youth with a disability, or multiple barriers to employment.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9ce4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Domestic violence, dating violence, sexual assault, stalking, and other dangerous, traumatic, or life-threatening conditions relating to such violence","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding any other provision of this section, the Secretary shall consider to be homeless any individual or family who—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9ce5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is experiencing trauma or a lack of safety related to, or fleeing or attempting to flee, domestic violence, dating violence, sexual assault, stalking, or other dangerous, traumatic, or life-threatening conditions related to the violence against the individual or a family member in the individual’s or family’s current housing situation, including where the health and safety of children are jeopardized;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9ce6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" has no other safe residence; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9ce7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" lacks the resources to obtain other safe permanent housing.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9ce8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Income eligibility","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9ce9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A homeless individual shall be eligible for assistance under any program provided by this chapter, only if the individual complies with the income eligibility requirements otherwise applicable to such program.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9cea-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Exception","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding paragraph (1), a homeless individual shall be eligible for assistance under title I of the Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s3111"},"text":"29 U.S.C. 3111","children":[],"tail":" et seq.]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9ceb-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Exclusion","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this chapter, the term “homeless” or “homeless individual” does not include any individual imprisoned or otherwise detained pursuant to an Act of the Congress or a State law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9cec-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11302/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Persons experiencing homelessness","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any references in this chapter to homeless individuals (including homeless persons) or homeless groups (including homeless persons) shall be considered to include, and to refer to, individuals experiencing homelessness or groups experiencing homelessness, respectively.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbf3d9ced-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/77/tI/s103"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–77, title I, § 103","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/485"},"text":"101 Stat. 485","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/625/tVIII/s822"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–625, title VIII, § 822","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-28"},"text":"Nov. 28, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/4355"},"text":"104 Stat. 4355","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/645/tVI/s602"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–645, title VI, § 602","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/4734"},"text":"104 Stat. 4734","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/dA/s101/f/tVIII/s405/d/41"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, div. A, § 101(f) [title VIII, § 405(d)(41), (f)(32)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/2681-337"},"text":"112 Stat. 2681–337","children":[],"tail":", 2681–427, 2681–434; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/22/dB/s1003/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–22, div. B, § 1003(a)","children":[],"tail":", title V, § 1502(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-05-20"},"text":"May 20, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/1664"},"text":"123 Stat. 1664","children":[],"tail":", 1701; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/128/tV/s512/s"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–128, title V, § 512(s)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/1712"},"text":"128 Stat. 1712","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/dW/tVI/s605/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, div. W, title VI, § 605(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-03-15"},"text":"Mar. 15, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/886"},"text":"136 Stat. 886","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbf3d9cee-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbf3d9cef-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbf3d9cf0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in subsecs. (a), (c)(1), (d), and (e), was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/77"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–77","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/482"},"text":"101 Stat. 482","children":[],"tail":", known as the McKinney-Vento Homeless Assistance Act, which is classified principally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s11301"},"text":"section 11301 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act, referred to in subsec. (c)(2), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/128"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–128","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/1425"},"text":"128 Stat. 1425","children":[],"tail":". Title I of the Act is classified generally to subchapter I (§ 3111 et seq.) of chapter 32 of Title 29, Labor. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s3101"},"text":"section 3101 of Title 29","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idbf3d9cf1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103","children":[],"tail":" amended subsec. (b) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “Notwithstanding any other provision of this section, the Secretary shall consider to be homeless any individual or family who is fleeing, or is attempting to flee, domestic violence, dating violence, sexual assault, stalking, or other dangerous or life-threatening conditions in the individual’s or family’s current housing situation, including where the health and safety of children are jeopardized, and who have no other residence and lack the resources or support networks to obtain other permanent housing.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2014—Subsec. (c)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/128"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–128","children":[],"tail":" substituted “a homeless individual shall be eligible for assistance under title I of the Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act” for “a homeless individual shall be eligible for assistance under title I of the Workforce Investment Act of 1998”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2009—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/22"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–22","children":[],"tail":" added subsecs. (a), (b), and (e), redesignated former subsecs. (b) and (c) as (c) and (d), respectively, and struck out former subsec. (a) which defined “homeless” or “homeless individual or homeless person”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1998—Subsec. (b)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/s101/f/tVIII/s405/f/32"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, § 101(f) [title VIII, § 405(f)(32)]","children":[],"tail":", struck out “the Job Training Partnership Act or” after “assistance under”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/s101/f/tVIII/s405/d/41"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, § 101(f) [title VIII, § 405(d)(41)]","children":[],"tail":", substituted “the Job Training Partnership Act or title I of the Workforce Investment Act of 1998” for “the Job Training Partnership Act”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/625"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–625","children":[],"tail":" inserted “or homeless person” after “homeless individual” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/645"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–645","children":[],"tail":" amended subsec. (b) generally. Prior to amendment, subsec. (b) read as follows: “A homeless individual shall be eligible for assistance under any program provided by this chapter, or by the amendments made by this Act, only if the individual complies with the income eligibility requirements otherwise applicable to such program.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idbf3d9cf2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idbf3d9cf3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2022 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103","children":[],"tail":" not effective until Oct. 1 of the first fiscal year beginning after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-03-15"},"text":"Mar. 15, 2022","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/dW/s4/a"},"text":"section 4(a) of div. W of Pub. L. 117–103","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s6851"},"text":"section 6851 of Title 15","children":[],"tail":", Commerce and Trade."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idbf3d9cf4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2014 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/128"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–128","children":[],"tail":" effective on the first day of the first full program year after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 2014","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 2015","children":[],"tail":"), see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/128/s506"},"text":"section 506 of Pub. L. 113–128","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s3101"},"text":"section 3101 of Title 29","children":[],"tail":", Labor."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idbf3d9cf5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2009 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/22/dB/tV/s1503"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–22, div. B, title V, § 1503","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-05-20"},"text":"May 20, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/1702"},"text":"123 Stat. 1702","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/111/22/dB/tV/s1503"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"section","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":""},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"“Except as specifically provided otherwise in this division [see Short Title of 2009 Amendment note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s11301"},"text":"section 11301 of this title","children":[],"tail":"], this division and the amendments made by this division shall take effect on, and shall apply beginning on—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the expiration of the 18-month period beginning on the date of the enactment of this division [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-05-20"},"text":"May 20, 2009","children":[],"tail":"], or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the expiration of the 3-month period beginning upon publication by the Secretary of Housing and Urban Development of final regulations pursuant to section 1504 [the first final regulations pursuant to section 1504 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s11301"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 11301","children":[],"tail":" note) were published on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-12-05"},"text":"Dec. 5, 2011","children":[],"tail":", see 76 F.R. 75994],"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"whichever occurs first.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idbf3d9cf6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1998 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by section 101(f) [title VIII, § 405(d)(41)] of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1998","children":[],"tail":", and amendment by section 101(f) [title VIII, § 405(f)(32)] of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 2000","children":[],"tail":", see section 101(f) [title VIII, § 405(g)(1), (2)(B)] of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s3502"},"text":"section 3502 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idbf3d9cf7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Regulations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/22/dB/s1003/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–22, div. B, § 1003(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-05-20"},"text":"May 20, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/1666"},"text":"123 Stat. 1666","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/111/22/dB/s1003/b"},"text":"“Not later than the expiration of the 6-month period beginning upon the date of the enactment of this division [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-05-20"},"text":"May 20, 2009","children":[],"tail":"], the Secretary of Housing and Urban Development shall issue regulations that provide sufficient guidance to recipients of funds under title IV of the McKinney-Vento Homeless Assistance Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s11360"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 11360","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] to allow uniform and consistent implementation of the requirements of section 103 of such Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s11302"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 11302","children":[],"tail":"], as amended by subsection (a) of this section. This subsection shall take effect on the date of the enactment of this division.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idbf400cf8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Clarification of Effect on Other Laws","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/22/dB/s1003/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–22, div. B, § 1003(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-05-20"},"text":"May 20, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/1666"},"text":"123 Stat. 1666","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/111/22/dB/s1003/c"},"text":"“This section [amending this section and enacting provisions set out as a note under this section] and the amendments made by this section to section 103 of the McKinney-Vento Homeless Assistance Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s11302"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 11302","children":[],"tail":") may not be construed to affect, alter, limit, annul, or supersede any other provision of Federal law providing a definition of ‘homeless’, ‘homeless individual’, or ‘homeless person’ for purposes other than such Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s11301"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 11301","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], except to the extent that such provision refers to such section 103 or the definition provided in such section 103.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
